cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.CV 

This paper is about teaching an agent to understand natural language in a simulated 3D environment. This involves combining reinforcement and unsupervised learning to enable the agent to relate linguistic symbols to perceptual representations of its surroundings and sequences of actions. The paper is likely to be categorized under cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing, followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). It also involves robotics (cs.RO) and computer vision (cs.CV) as the agent interacts with its environment and perceives visual information.
